cruise, but you're seasick and you omit that

00:02:13.560 --> 00:02:15.569
from the post -- white lie, brah.

00:02:15.569 --> 00:02:19.950
Whether these are pro-social white lies, or
antisocial white lies depends on who they're

00:02:19.950 --> 00:02:20.950
targeting.

00:02:20.950 --> 00:02:23.629
And the intent of the post…

00:02:23.629 --> 00:02:27.689
The Journal of Consumer Research found that
even though they're beneficial to the whole,

00:02:27.689 --> 00:02:31.069
white lies FEEL like lies to our brain.

00:02:31.069 --> 00:02:36.650
We KNOW we're being dishonest, so we try to
fix it, or make up for our dishonesty to escape

00:02:36.650 --> 00:02:37.890
cognitive dissonance.

00:02:37.890 --> 00:02:41.669
Cognitive dissonance is when your brain thinks
one thing and you act differently.

00:02:41.669 --> 00:02:47.390
Like if a bad server at a restaurant asks
how your meal was -- usually, we lie.

00:02:47.390 --> 00:02:50.560
We save the waiters feelings and keep things
on an even keel!

00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:54.879
According to research into cognitive dissonance,
unless the service was REALLY bad, we will

00:02:54.879 --> 00:02:59.180
often tip more because we want to make up
for our white lie!

00:02:59.180 --> 00:03:01.799
It's silly, but it happens on a subconscious
level.

00:03:01.799 --> 00:03:05.010
It's part of our evolution trying to keep
our social networks balanced.

